@NODE Requirements
@{B}Requirements@{UB}

- AmigaOS 2.04 or better (not Windows, of course).

@ENDNODE

@NODE Installation
@{B}How To Install@{UB}

There are two ways to install WinRes.  One way is to use the
'Install_WinRes' script came with the archive.  This will work only if
you have Workbench 3.0 or better.  Just double-click the icon and it
will ask you where to install WinRes.  It would be a good idea to
install WinRes to be in your system path (e.g.  C:, SYS:Utilities).

This documentation and related files will not be installed by the
installer.

The other way is to install it manually.  Just use CLI command 'Copy' or
directory utility such as DirectoryOpus to place anywhere you want.  For
example,

> Copy WinRes C:

will copy WinRes to C:  if you typed this in the same directory where
WinRes executable is.  Please refer to AmigaDOS manual if you need more
help.

I have included 'Uninstall_WinRes' just in case somebody might want to
uninstall from the hard drive.  Just double-click the icon to perform
uninstallation.

@ENDNODE

@NODE Usage
@{B}How To Use@{UB}

You can only use this program from CLI.


@{U}Template@{UU}

WinRes FILE/A,V=VERBOSE/S

FILE/A  : name of the resource file to extract from (.EXE, .DLL, .ICL,
          etc.).
VERBOSE : displays lots of information about the resource file.  A good
          way to find out what's in it.

All the files will be extracted to the CLI's current directory.
Currently only the .ICO files will be extracted and the names will be
based on their ID number contained in the resource file.


@{U}Examples@{UU}

> WinRes CITYFAR.ICL

This will extract all the icons from 'CITYFAR.ICL'.

> WinRes VERBOSE SETUP.EXE

This will extract all the icons from 'SETUP.EXE' and display information
about the file.

@ENDNODE

